Package: ggshadow
Title: Shadow Geoms for ggplot2
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Marc", "Menem", email = "marc.menem@m4x.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implement geom_shadowpath(), geom_shadowline(), geom_shadowstep() and geom_shadowpoint() for 'ggplot2'.
             These functions draw a shadow below points or lines to make busy plots more aesthetically pleasing.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    grid,
    scales
Suggests:
    knitr,
    prettydoc
VignetteBuilder: knitr
License: GPL-2 | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/marcmenem/ggshadow/
BugReports: https://github.com/marcmenem/ggshadow/issues
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Collate: 
    'geom-shadowpath.r'
    'geom-shadowpoint.r'
